parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall Delays and Inefficiencies
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing or replacing defective airbags can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are unavailable
dealerships are unresponsive or unhelpful
and repairs are delayed or cannot be scheduled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning indicator may indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities if not addressed.
symptoms: Airbag warning indicator illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and harsh shifting can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission and engine.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle jerks or bucks when shifting
the transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the "AT" light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch plate falls apart
the clutch makes a noise or vibrates when pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission fluid pressure sensor/switch failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission and engine.
symptoms: The transmission fluid pressure sensor/switch fails
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the "AT" light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Torque Converter Clutch Pressure Control Solenoid Intermittent Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The torque converter clutch pressure control solenoid intermittent failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and damage to the transmission and engine.
symptoms: The torque converter clutch pressure control solenoid fails intermittently
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the "AT" light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to veer off course, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel independently veers to one side
the vehicle pulls to one side without being able to control it
the steering wheel makes horrible sounds when turning
the steering wheel clunks when turning
the steering wheel is crooked but the vehicle is not out of alignment
the vehicle locks up when placed in reverse.
